  "description": [
    "Another War Book by Simonds Every day since last July you have been reading war newsas news In the confusion of varying reports you have often turned to the clear vision of the war editorials by Frank II Simonds as they appeared first in the livening Sun and are now appearing in The Tribune If you read his first book The Great War which attracted nationwide comment and appreciation you know the importance of the announce ment that his second book THE GREAT WAR THE SECOND PHASE has just been published It covers the course of events from the fall of Antwerp to the second battle of Ypres It crystallixs the meaning of a thousand dispatches vv T s i naaOmaaw r m e With the fall of Antwerp the war passed into its second phase The German Army was firmly entrenched along the Aisne in the Western sphere of war On the eastern boundary the Russian bear had grasped Lembcrg and Jaroslav He had suffered at Tannenbergbut he was rising on his shaggy hind legs No announcement of this new book by Mr Simonds could worthily show the setting of the second act of the worlds mos colossal drama"
  ],
